descript.abstract: This data set shows management units for deer and other wildlife in New York, beginning with the 2009/2010 season.
descript.purpose: To provide a digital representation of Wildlife Management Units in New York State.
descript.supplinf:
1. Wildlife Management Units are not changed every year. The Habitat Inventory Unit maintains the current version of the Wildlife Management Units.
2. This dataset replaces the previous Wildlife Management Units used for the 1998/1999 through 2008/2009 season. For these previous units see Wildlife Management Unit 1998-99.
3. This layer lacks additional non-WMU boundaries that partially define the Northern hunting area for Black Bear, and the antler point restriction area for Deer. For further information please contact the Habitat Inventory Unit.
4. The DeLorme atlas with highlighted features used as references for the creation of the new WMU boundaries is kept by Sherry Mickle (Wildlife Services Team, Albany) .
5. The management unit boundary lines are generally based on 1:100,000 scale digital line graph data.
6. Several edits have been made to the WMU data set subsequent to its initial publication in 2009. Please see Process Steps for details.

procstep.procdesc: Bob Sanford (Wildlife Services Team, Delmar) provided legal descriptions of the unit boundaries (with changes from the old DMU boundaries highlighted).
Regional wildlife staff provided DeLorme Atlases with the boundaries drawn for Regions 3-9.

An older DeLorme Atlas prepared by John Palmateer (Big Game Unit, retired) that had been used in the preparation of previous Deer Management Unit coverages was also referred to for boundaries that were not expected to change from existing DMU boundaries, and thus may not have been drawn in the new atlases from the Regions.

An ArcInfo coverage of the boundaries was constructed in Arcedit, primarily using arcs selected from 1:100,000 scale coverages of roads and hydrography based on USGS Digital Line Graph data. In a few cases where the 1:100,000 scale data were inadequate to represent the boundary, some boundaries were digitized from images of 1:24,000 scale NYSDOT planimetric maps.

cntperp.cntorg: NYSDEC Division of Fish, Wildlife & Marine Resources, Habitat Inventory Unit

procstep.procdesc: Bill Hoffman (Wildlife Services Team, Albany) provided legal descriptions and a DeLorme atlas showing WMU boundary changes for the 2009/2010 season. Gordon Batcheller (Wildlife Services Team, Albany) later provided a legal description and map for an additional change.
The Feature Class to Feature Class tool was used to convert the polygons of the WMU coverage to a geodatabase feature class.

cntperp.cntorg: NYSDEC Division of Fish, Wildlife & Marine Resources, Habitat Inventory Unit
NYSDEC Division of Fish, Wildlife & Marine Resources, Habitat Inventory Unit

procstep.procdesc: In ArcMap, road segments needed to construct the new WMU boundaries were selected from the Road, 1:100,000 layer of the Master Habitat Data Bank and exported to geodatabase feature classes. In cases where the necessary road segments could not be obtained from Road, 1:100,000 layer, the Roads, ALIS layer was used instead. Using Construct Features on the Topology toolbar, the road segments were used to split the WMU polygons along the new boundaries. The Merge function from the Editor menu was then used to merge polygons on either side of the old boundaries. The value of the UNITSQMILES field was then recalculated from SHAPE.AREA.

Standard fields carried over from the old ArcInfo WMU coverage were deleted from the WMU polygon feature class. The Dissolve tool was used to dissolve the WMU polygon feature class on the UNIT field with a statistic of FIRST on the UNITSQMILES field and "Create multipart features" checked. A new UNITSQMILES field was added and calculated equal to FIRST_UNITSQMILES; the FIRST_UNITSQMILES field was then deleted.

cntperp.cntorg: NYSDEC Division of Fish, Wildlife & Marine Resources, Habitat Inventory Unit
NYSDEC Division of Fish, Wildlife & Marine Resources, Habitat Inventory Unit

procstep.procdesc: Numerous edits were made to the WMU feature class, mostly to undo previously proposed WMU boundary changes. One new WMU boundary change was also made.
An error in the southern border of WMU 9P was corrected.
